\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 76. A. giennensis} Heywood,{\i   Feddes Repert.}{\b  79}: 50 (1968). Like {\b 75}(d) but more robust, with stronger spines; leaflets 6-9 pairs, less densely hairy; peduncles c. 1 cm; bracts lanceolate or linear-lanceolate, with 1-2 distinct lateral veins; calyx-teeth about twice as long as tube; corolla pale purplish. •{\i   S.E. Spain }({\i  Prov. Jaen}). Hs.
